    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What are Responsive Images?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Responsive images adapt to different screen sizes and resolutions, improving performance and user experience."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Using srcset Attribute"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<img src=\"small.jpg\"\n     srcset=\"small.jpg 500w, medium.jpg 1000w, large.jpg 1500w\"\n     sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 500px, (max-width: 1200px) 1000px, 1500px\"\n     alt=\"Responsive Image\">"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Using Picture Element"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<picture>\n  <source media=\"(max-width: 600px)\" srcset=\"small.jpg\">\n  <source media=\"(max-width: 1200px)\" srcset=\"medium.jpg\">\n  <img src=\"large.jpg\" alt=\"Responsive Image\">\n</picture>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "How srcset Works"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The browser selects the most appropriate image based on device width, resolution, and the sizes attribute."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Sizes Attribute"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Defines how much space the image will take in different viewport conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 50vw\""
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Art Direction with Picture"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "The picture element allows you to show completely different images for different screen sizes."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<picture>\n  <source media=\"(max-width: 600px)\" srcset=\"mobile.jpg\">\n  <source media=\"(min-width: 601px)\" srcset=\"desktop.jpg\">\n  <img src=\"default.jpg\" alt=\"Art Direction\">\n</picture>"
    },
